Backend Engineering Design DocumentCandidate: Backend Developer Intern ApplicantProject: Scalable Auth & CRUD System1. System ArchitectureThe backend is designed using a Modular Monolith approach to balance simplicity and future scalability.Express.js / NestJS: For robust routing and middleware support.PostgreSQL: Chosen for relational integrity, support for complex RBAC queries, and ACID compliance.Redis: Implemented as a caching layer for JWT blacklisting and frequently accessed entity data.Docker: Containerized for consistent deployment across dev/prod environments.2. Database Schema (PostgreSQL)Table: usersColumnTypeConstraintsidUUIDPrimary Key, Default: gen_random_uuid()emailVARCHAR(255)Unique, Not Nullpassword_hashTEXTNot NullnameVARCHAR(100)Not NullroleENUM('user', 'admin')Default: 'user'created_atTIMESTAMPDefault: now()Table: tasksColumnTypeConstraintsidBIGSERIALPrimary Keyuser_idUUIDForeign Key -> users(id), ON DELETE CASCADEtitleVARCHAR(255)Not NullstatusENUM('pending', 'completed')Default: 'pending'priorityENUM('low', 'medium', 'high')Default: 'medium'3. API Versioning & RoutingFollowing REST principles with v1 versioning.POST /api/v1/auth/register: User signup (password hashing with bcrypt).POST /api/v1/auth/login: Issues JWT.GET /api/v1/tasks: List tasks. (Users see own, Admin sees all).POST /api/v1/tasks: Create task (Validation with Joi/Zod).PATCH /api/v1/tasks/:id: RBAC Check: Ensure userId === currentUserId OR role === 'admin'.4. Scalability & Security Best PracticesPassword Hashing: Bcrypt with a cost factor of 12.JWT Security: Stored in HttpOnly cookies to prevent XSS. 15-minute expiry with Refresh Tokens stored in DB.Rate Limiting: express-rate-limit to prevent brute force on /login.Input Validation: Strict schema validation on all POST/PATCH bodies to prevent SQL Injection and malformed data.Logging: Integrated Winston or Morgan for tracking API latency and error rates.API Documentation: Auto-generated Swagger (OpenAPI 3.0) accessible at /api-docs.5. Deployment ReadinessDocker Compose: Orchestrates Node, Postgres, and Redis.CI/CD: GitHub Actions for linting, unit testing (Jest), and automated container builds.Monitoring: Integration-ready for Prometheus/Grafana or Datadog.